cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with depth and ego motion estimation from monocular images. The use of deep learning models for image sampling and estimation also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on motion estimation and use of geometric constraints could also suggest that it belongs to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of the KITTI dataset and experimental analysis suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
